Property "rowCount" does not work, tested with SDK 3.0.2.GA

Seems like value is not set in TiUIDashboardView.m:

{code:xml}
int rowCount = [TiUtils intValue:[self.proxy valueForKey:@"rowCount"] def:kDashboardViewDefaultRowCount];
NSLog(@"### rowCount: %d", rowCount);
{code}

Always returned the predefined number.

Curiously columnCount works properly.

Also see https://developer.appcelerator.com/question/149207/columncount-and-rowcount-do-not-work-well-in-dashboardview

I don't use Alloy and of course I set the property in the creation statement:

{code}
var dashboard = Ti.UI.createDashboardView({
	data: data, // previously created and saved to array
	rowCount: 2,
	columnCount: 3,
	wobble: true,
	top: 60,
	height: 250
});
{code}

h4.code for testing

{code}

var items = [[], [], []];

for (var j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
  for (var i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
    var item = Ti.UI.createDashboardItem();
    item.add(Ti.UI.createLabel({
      text: "item numba " + i,
      borderColor: '#'+i+'0'+i+'000',
      borderWidth: 3,
      height: 'fill', width: 'fill'
    }));
    items[j][i] = item;
  }
}

var dashboard = Ti.UI.createDashboardView({
    data: items[0], // previously created and saved to array
    rowCount: 2,
    columnCount: 3,
    wobble: true,
    top: 60,
    height: 250
});

var win = Ti.UI.createWindow({
	backgroundColor:'white',
});
win.add(dashboard);
win.open();

{code}
